Stateless:
Every req. to server is treated as the first request btw you and the server.

Stateless flow: [ 
Login(user send username/pass to server)---> 
Verify(server check db to see if username/pass {called credentials} are correct or no)----> 
Token Creation(server create token/JWT (on for access and other for refresh) that contains user info + secret key {Header.payload.Signature}) --->
Token handing (server send JWT to user {so no data is stored in server now})---->
User next Req (user send new req. and with each req. attach the JWT (which is saved in local storage) in Authorization headers)-->
Server validation (Server recieves JWT and check cryptographic signature if valid the respond)-->
Response (Server sends the requested data)
 ]


